<br>
Tha kitties on the moon are in a state of war against the grimling hoardes, a plight most sympathetic given our own Norrathian problems with orcs and goblins. I know that Captain Necin in the Var Shir outpost in the Grimling Forest has need of an army, and that to prove your worth ta him ya must first engage in three military campaigns. His quest is part of tha process of obtaining keys ta the Grimling Fortress tucked away inside Acylia Caverns, a key that I suspect both of our armies would appreciate adding our resources.<br>
<br>
So I propose that we mount the forces ta fight two concurrantly running Grimling Wars. Each war consists of three battles, the most furious of which will require two full groups of heros in their fourties. We can develop a structure so that we fight Husman's Raid and Danarin's Raid as a full force, which should make us barely break a sweat. Then our combined forces can conduct Derrin's Raid as a full force, which will be a bit more of a logistical challenge. Then we can break into two forces, fighting both Husman's and Danarin's raids again simultaneously, then regroup fer a final Derrin's raid.<br>
<br>
This likely means three to four hours of warfare, and would require at least 18 heros in their 40s, or perhaps more if the force is younger, but it should be accomplishable. Both the Elven Elite and Champions could designate keyholders to whom the rewards of the quests are assigned, and we could make a commitment to each other that we pull out the battles we need for two complete sets.<br>
<br>
If energy remains, we could then be even more daring and move into Acrylia Caverns itself. The enemy there is quite dangerous, and the encounters are best suited fer heros far our elder. But with a raid sized force, it could mean a succession of battles as fearsum as Tserrina herself to test a more traditional main assist strategy with.<br>
<br>
I will take my leave of you for now, Debba ... but leave for you these scrolls to peruse to consider this potential campaign.<br>
<br>
On Captain Necin's Challenge:<br>
