<br>
&quot;What's this I smell?  Another of my brethren, come out from the underfoot?  Good ta see ya, Gnostik!&quot;<br>
<br>
After hearing more about the possibility of slaughtering a few of the heathen grimlings (as well as drinking his current stout, plus the drinks of anyone foolish enough to leave them sitting around), he was a bit, shall we say, excited.<br>
<br>
&quot;Bring 'dem critters on!  I'll keel them all, I tell you, KEEL THEM ALL!!!&quot;<br>
<br>
Shortly afterwards, Blahg &quot;sat&quot; down in the corner and &quot;slept&quot; for a day or two, finally stirring as a bucket of cold water was poured over him.<br>
<br>
/ooc In any case.....   Please make sure I hear about this when we do it.  I'd absolutely love to keel a few of those heathen grimlings.  Just the thought of them, living in the underfoot as though they fancy themselves cousins to the glorious children of Brell, makes me hungry for grimling blood...  or whatever else may run through their veins.<br>
